content.detailedDescription: About 5:50 pm on sunday dec. 14, 2014 was leaving my condo and spotted at first maybe 5 of these round lights moving across the sky over the ocean (long beach, ca)north east.  were soon joined by more. the lights appeared to be moving only a bit faster than helicopter speed, but hard to say because i had no idea how big or how far away they might be.. but appeared within maybe a 1/2 mile and flying relatively low altitude. three of the lights went into a triangle formation, then another set of 3 did the same. just before they seemingly dissolved, and disappeared, they seemed to become a small white dot and i could almost make out a craft form before they shot off at amazing speed. they did this at different points in time, and seemed to go different directions. as i watched and headed downstairs (2nd floor balcony walkway) i continued to watch. a man approached me almost immediately ranting about the ufo's i'd been observing. as i rode off on my bike, one of the orange sperical lights remained.. and i continued to watch it for another five minutes or so. this is the first time i've ever seen something like this, (52 years old), and i thought sure there would be hundreds of reports on it, but i have not seen one anywhere after looking extensively. very strange.
content.summary: Close to a dozen red spherical lights changing to orange. formed 2 triangles of 3 seperate lights. very obvious in sky. lasted mayb 5-10 minutes.

content.detailedDescription: I was outside of my house at 10:50 pm smoking while speaking on the phone and noticed something huge above my house. thats when i looked up and saw this huge triangular black ufo passing by slowly. i've never seen something like it. it didn't made any sound and i could see the traits of the ufo. i could compare it with the suit of spiderman ( the weird lines on his suit ) and the lights where completely red.  3 lights on each end and i could see something on the center of the ufo. i felt scared but amazed at the same time. it was heading west.
content.summary: Black triangular ufo with red light at each end and something on the middle.

content.detailedDescription:
Driving north on n delbert rd late morning. partially cloudy. near intersection of county line rd. i observed a large, distant bright white aerial object about 20 degrees above rooftops. it hovered and then made a large arcing path movement, then hovered. it appeared to be constantly shape shifting. my first thought was a pelican, which nest in the landfills near highway i-25. but the way it hovered in one place and seemed to be constantly changing shape made this unlikely. also at the observed distance it would have to be a pelican the size of a prop plane. 

i watched this object remain stationary yet changing shape for a good 4-5 minutes as i traveled north. i then observed two fighter jets in tight formation come in from the right (east) flying relatively low (enough to see details of underside).  they flew overhead and made a sharp curve northeast which put them in the direction of the white object, though they were still some distance from it.  as they kept on course, now by perspective "close" to the object (far in distance but side by side in vision) the white object disintegrated. in about ten seconds the object just faded into nothing. it did not move, or sink. it literally looked like a movie special effect where it just dissolved into nothing.

the fighter jets broke their formation after the object disappeared and went east and west, respectively. the area i live in, east aurora co is home to buckley afb. fighter jets, huge air carriers and military helicopters flying low are a daily occurrence.   they are so loud that they shake the house, and i have observed many different interesting aircraft flying around here, but nothing like what i saw that thursday.  i also have never seen the fighter jets fly in that tight side by side formation, one slightly in front of the other. i have seen the four unit formation and single jets, as well as a few flying a good distance apart but nothing like the flight behavior i saw that day.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Large bright white shape shifting aerial object.

content.detailedDescription: Sunday october 20, 2013 i was driving north on i75/85 and had just passed atl hartsfield airport when i glanced up through the open sunroof and noticed what looked like a bright daytime star and a second delta/chevron-shaped darker object directly overhead at apparent great altitude.  the airplane flight paths are farther south of the sighting location and run east-west so there were no planes immediately visible, but significant highway noise.  i pulled the car over to end of next on-ramp immediately north of airport and noted time at 4:19 pm.  the daytime "star" was easily visible (not extremely faint as might be expected, if at all detectable during the day) and seemed stationary the entire time.  the delta-shaped object was pointed toward the "star" and initially about 9" away from the "star" at arms length.  the left "wing" of the delta object was a dull metallic grayish color while the right side appeared dark red color.  size of the delta object was approx 1/4" at arms length.  for the entire 7 minute sighting, the delta object held perfectly steady in terms of speed, northwesterly direction, and apparent altitude.  no bobbing, swaying, dipping, change in yaw, or other motion except to move very slowly and steadily toward the "star", always keeping its nose pointed directly toward the "star".  after approx 7 minutes the delta object was approx 2" at arms length from the "star".  at that point a large cloudbank (est 8,000 feet?) which had been approaching from the east in a west/southwesterly direction blocked my view of the objects.  i estimated it would be 20 minutes before the cloudbank moved over and i was not stopped in a safe spot, so i continued driving north, stopping approx 10 miles north to look skyward again, but saw nothing.  i checked the news that night and the following day to see if anyone else had reported these but found nothing.  what is particularly odd is these were directly above the busiest airport in the world, at apparent high altitude, and the delta object moved in a direction other than the cloud-level winds, steadily at only 1" per minute at arms length.  i have excellent vision and had a very clear view for approx 7 minutes.  my thought is hartsfield must have had it/them on radar unless they were well above the 60,000 foot controlled airspace ceiling.  it did occur to be at great altitude.  no guess as to what the delta/chevron object was but clearly not a plane or other conventional aircraft.  the "star" could have been a star, but so bright during the daylight?  and coincidental that the delta object was moving directly toward it?  wish i had my video camera at the time...
content.summary: Apparent daytime stationary star above atl airport approached steadily by chevron/delta shaped object over 7 minute period

content.detailedDescription:
During 4th of july we saw numerous circular and one large triangular
craft (which smaller glowing craft emerged) travel toward us from ne to sw
emerging from distant fireworks displays. our town, however, had postponed
our fireworks due to bad weather (they were probably trying to hide within the fireworks, but when our northern town's display stopped the objects flew over us slowly and completely quiet. my wife noticed smaller objects coming from the large triangular craft, helicopter-like. the smaller craft
glowed with no distinguishable definition. there were about a dozen large
definitely circular craft brightly lit orange with red, circular bottoms.
i was so stunned i forgot about my camera as they slowly moved toward ny area sw. this lasted some 15 to 20 minutes with them ruling the sky.
once they were out on the area, suddenly regular air traffic continued.
(there were no other aircraft in the area up until this time.)
i figure that the glowing objects (no definite outline) are theirs and the lighted, definitive objects are ours. 
  some local residents also witnessed this but had no comments.
content.summary: Fleet moving slow to sw, overhead

content.detailedDescription:
The entire family is well trained in astro and scientific observations. i am a trained advanced expert for the us government. i personally observed what i thought was the reflection of our teenaged son's x-box. the lights were not from his room. others in our house, all phd's or very well qualified persons, all agreed that this was unusual. the volk field is a usafb about 1/8 mile from our house. we have observed stealth helo's and umv's before. the family is very well versed on all aspects of aerial aircraft.

the observation was marked with feeling sick today. exchanging of unusual lights, neighbors reporting seeing a hovering craft near-by.

my security clearance is e-8. i guess no longer...... very unusual.
content.summary: Very unusual, trained darpa person

content.detailedDescription:
On december 17, 2014, at about 6 pm i went to pickup my wife at the main entrance of "las americas mall" 7795 west flagler street, in miami, florida. 
when coming back home and driving through fontainebleau boulevard, two blocks west of park boulevard, at 6:50 pm, my wife shouted from the van front passenger seat, very loud: "what is that!!!  a flying saucer??? i immediately looked and saw a large object, 100 to 200 ft in size, completely stationary at about 1,500 ft. in altitude, hovering right in the path of several planes that were landing at that very moment all coming to the airport from the west.
we are absolutely sure that the pilots were looking at the object, as it was right in front of them. airplanes were landing at least on two of the three runways the miami international airport has for planes coming from the west.
the object was illuminated very bright in yellow or gold light and changing to green light with regularity. it had approximately the shape of a blimp.
after some minutes the object went dark, the lights went off.
then the lights came back and the object suddenly accelerated directly up, at a very high rate of speed, disappearing from our sight.
there was no cloud cover. we had total visibility.
at first i thought the object may have been a blimp, but i have never seen a blimp that illuminates their whole surface in such a bright light and also changing colors or going totally dark, precisely sitting at a place where planes are landing.
on the other hand, it will be absurd for a blimp to sit stationary right on the path of several landing planes. the miami international airport has three landing runways for planes coming from the west. the object was over the one in the middle. also, blimps cannot accelerate suddenly the way this object did. and certainly not go up and go away in a second.
at that very moment, there was a huge plane landing on the main runway, the runway placed at the south of the airport. before going up and away, the object was to the right of that airplane from our point of view. the pilot must have seen the object to his left, like half a mile away from him, at about 6:55 pm on december 17, 2014.
content.summary: Bright object stationary over airplanes landing at miami int'l airport

content.detailedDescription: Was driving home headed southwest and noticed two star like objects very bright, above each other. maybe top one was at 1 o'clock position. then saw the top star move clockwise towards a 3 o'clock position. as i was diving i thought i would come towards them but they were actually moving off in same direction as me. headed sw down the gulf coast of fl. tried to keep an eye on them but treeline got in the way. i was in northport when i first saw them, headed to port charlotte. they were very bright in starlike color. when i finally got to sr 776, i couldn't tell where they were as after the initial split they moved off in two different directions though heading sw. thought it was odd and actually thought about calling air traffic control at punta gorda airport but thought that would be a waste of time as i probably wouldn't get the information i was seeking.
content.summary: Two star like objects in sw sky, one above eachother then uppermost rotated to left as they proceded a sw path.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking onto the bolehill recreation ground to catch up with a group of friends whom were already on the playground section when i saw a red light out of the corner of my eye. when i looked up almost directly above me was a large black triangular solid object with a red light in the middle moving very slowly and very low from my left to my right. there was absolutely no sound at all which was puzzling as the object was so close to the ground. as it passed my field of vision from the left i noticed on what i considered to be the rear of the object an arrangement of what looked like three exhausts you might find on an f14 jetfighter but in a triangular formation unlike any i have seen before and emitting a white light. these remained visible as the object continued overhead and disappeared into the distance. i was dumbstruck and didnt ask my friends if they had seen it too as i thought if they had they would have said something which none of them did.I headed straight home without telling anyone what i had seen and i have wondered what it was ever since.Also about half an hour before i saw this object i felt and heard a low humming sound in the same area that i witnessed this object.
content.summary: Solid triangular object passing very slowly and very low overhead disappearing over horizon

content.detailedDescription: I was in san pedro california with my sister, as i was taking pictures of the beautiful view i had i noticed something was off in the sky. so i proceeded to take more pictures and i realized there was a domino effect of light in the sky. at first i thought maybe something was reflecting off the floor but there couldn't have been because beneath the object was the ocean. when i kept looking at the object it started moving nw within a mater of seconds it literally disappeared into the clouds. i was more excited and amazed more than anything because i have never seen anything like it before. the object just disappeared into the clouds.
content.summary: Very short timing

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting watching tv in living room when i noticed a bright glowing object through the trees in the first window, then i saw it go into view through the next window. by the time i saw it in the third window and saw it drop a piece of liquid then realized what it could and probably was, i had to get the dog down out of my lap, get up out of the chair and look out the window to see where it was going it was gone. went out through the back garage but, it was still not visible. so i went back in and tried to see if there was any thing on the mn mufon site as to what it might be or a link to a web site where someone could see what might be falling from the skies that night but, no luck. in my best opinion i believe that it was something like a hot melting craft. you could see the heat that it had and when it dropped something straight down instead of like it falling to the rear while it was moving that sort of sealed the deal for me that it was something of interest. i had seen something similar to this back on august 19, 1993. i was thinking that at first it might of been a low falling meteorite or something but, when i saw the dripping come down out of it i knew that it couldn't be certain things that i was thinking it might be. i got up and told about it at the mn mufon monthly meeting
content.summary: Glowing hot disk shape object moving south to north and dropped a piece of like hot liquid metal.

content.detailedDescription:
I had just walked outside to have a cigarette at 5:47 when i looked to the east sky as i am an avid star gazer. there was minimal cloud cover to the south and the sky was dark enough to observe stars in the background. at approximately 60 degrees above the horizon to the east i noticed 5 lights blinking in succession starting with the one furthest to my south and extending approximately 90 degrees evenly across my field of view to the north. my initial thought was that it might be a satellite, but surprisingly there was also a satellite streaking across the sky from the north-east heading south-west. this provided me with a reference for atmospheric conditions and distance. the satellite maintained light characteristics and moved at a constant speed behind the blinking lights. thus the blinking lights had to be within the distance from earth to the satellite.  

at this point i felt very excited by what i was witnessing and called into the house for my girlfriend to come and observe. she came within 10 seconds and also observed the same phenomena. 

seconds later i noticed a military plane coming from the north with solid red and green lights. the jet followed in the direction of the blinking lights, and when it past my view directly east i could hear the jet engine. at this time the 5 lights were still traversing in a south-east direction but started to turn more east, also the pattern in which the blink changed to be more random than sequential. each blink lasted a fraction of a second, with time in between blinks ranging from 1 to 3 seconds. when first observed the lights were arranged linearly, but as i witnessed them moving more east the line of lights changed to more of a random configuration, this led me to think the 5 lights were in fact separate objects rather than one. 

i eventually lost sight of the objects behind the southern cloud cover, though i could still hear the jet engine from the plane for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. 

after the sighting i felt very energized and ecstatic. it was a good feeling and not one of anxiety or nerves. i kept thinking to myself "no way i have never seen anything like this before". 

my background in observation is two-fold. first i was a trained seamen in the us navy from 2004-2008 where i achieved the rank of e-5. my job was a quartermaster, making weather observations and identifying aircraft on lookout. secondly, in college i took multiple astronomy classes in which we made astronomical observations and have witnessed on many occasions satellites. this sighting is something i have never witnessed before.
content.summary: 5 pulsating lights traveling se being followed by aircraft

content.detailedDescription: My mom and i were driving home on 422 eastbound on 12/15/14 just passed the morgantown expressway 176 route in reading, pennsylvania. it was roughly about 7:30 pm. off to the right as soon as we got over the bridge right past the 176 exit was a large round sparkling lit object hovering down in the woods right by the schuykill river. i've never seen lights so sparkling and crystal reflective like. the ufo was round with about 30 of sparkling lights around the edge of the ufo. i only was able to view it for about 5 seconds because i was driving. i asked my mom who was with me, "did you see that?" at first i thought i was seeing things but she affirmed she had also seen it too and she seemed in shock. the brightness and sparkling quality of the lights were extraordinary and like nothing i've ever seen in my life. it reminded of only something you see in abstract art and heavenly spiritual like experiences. it just hovered or landed down in the woods. there was a search light close by and my mom thought they were looking for something. i was just in shock and asked my mom if she minded if i drove back around to see it again. she just wanted to get home. i had a dream that night that i was implanted with robotic parts in the back of my calf. my mom and daughters were in the dream. they too were implanted some weird devices. i woke up with weird indents on my wrist like i had been laying on a zipper but i just had pajama on. there was a rust like residual in the creases of the indents that wouldn't come off. my daughter woke up with a 1/4 inch sore on her wrist and was complaining of having calf pain. i didn't tell her anything about my dream or ufo experience. she also said she felt spacey yesterday just out of the blue. she has never said anything like that before. she is 13 years old. about 5 days ago there was a knock on our front window in the middle of the night and no one was there. 3 days ago there was lights on in certain rooms that we were sure we had turned off. also, our dogs have been barking as if there is something in the house over the last two-three days. i've had ufo experiences in the past and often dream of alien abductions. i have a pit hole dead center on my spinal column about half way down my back. this was not always there either. i've always felt we were from this earth and had a visit from a man in black the day following one of my ufo sightings. he was dressed in black, had a suitcase, came in the store i was in, waited outside the store for about 45 minutes and approached me asking questions about bus pickups. it was very odd.
content.summary: Circular sparkling lit ufo in woods by river

content.detailedDescription: The night i witnessed the 2 objects i was walking from outside to get to a study session when i happened to look up because something caught my eye. living in the colorado mountains you often see shooting stars, satalites so i looked up to catch it. what i saw stunned me, there were two objects moving towards each other in a very controlled fashion. once they became close they began to circle one another a few times. after this they quickly dashed away in opposite directions. i have served time in the us air force and have seen many craft in the air. also i have witnessed shooting stars, satalites, chinese lanterns and other events in the sky living in colorado and this event was like nothing i had ever experienced in my life.The event took a total of about 3 minutes but it held my attention every second. i attempted to take picture evidence but my cell phone camera did not have the capability to take a night photo. it was truly an unexplainable event which to a person that has seen and heard many air craft varients at day and night is still keeping me wondering.
content.summary: Two objects, moving towards each other, circled each other quickly, exited in opposite directions

content.detailedDescription: While looking around your site, i decided to go ahead and report something that happened long ago. i was lead radar operator at the time aboard the uss tolovana ao64. we were operating in the northern pacfic southeast of russia and east of japan. i am not sure of the month or year but the time frame of autumn 1971 should be close. i was on watch at the time and was manning our spa-4 radar. i reported to the bridge that i had a contact coming toward us out of the ne at the unbelievable speed of 750 knots. a couple of minutes later the bridge responded that they had a visual on blinking red lights. watching the scope i calculated that the contact came to an abrupt stop at a range of 2000 yds. the bridge responded with confirmation that the craft was hovering. it was observed by myself on radar and by the bridge visually, to hover about 5 minutes. then just as suddenly as it appeared, i tracked it move to the east at 750 knots. as i recall, i was sweeping at a range of less than 50 miles. the spa-4 was a surface radar that would not detect at a very high altitude. the visual horizon from the bridge was about 15 miles. when i first saw the craft on radar it was approximately 30 miles away. hope this can be of some help even though it was a long time ago.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription: I was sleeping in my bed and the whole room was filled by super bright light.I woke up thinking it was daytime & i got out of bed and went to look out the side window.The whole neighborhood didn't look real,i didn't see any cars or trees!The light was brighter than it should be.I turned around and looked at the clock on the nightstand under the front window,it was 4am.I wasn't scared at any time during my experience.After looking at the clock,i remember looking out the window and saying the word no over and over again.  eventually my older brother told me to shut up and get back in bed.I looked at the clock,it was only 4:11am.I looked out the window at the big fiery planet like object above the church at the end of our street.Everything still looked very strange and not real.I heard my brother tell me to shut up again.I turned to tell him about the big planet,he and my younger brother were no longer in the bedroom.It was still only 4:11am.I turned around and looked back out the window at the big reddish-orange planet like object above the guardian angels church.I wondered if it was like the one i saw when i was 3-4 yrs old.Anyway it just hovered above the church.The next thing i remember,i woke up.Didn't know if what i saw was real or a dream.My brothers were back in there beds!I didn't really talk too much about it until later on in life.One night my best friend and i were talking about u.F.O.S and alien life.We each talked about what each other went through and i realized it  wasn't a dream!!I didn't know what happened until i started writing about it,and my brother told me he saw the ship that was surrounding the big reddish-orange planet like object.He said it looked mechanical and and it covered the whole sky as far as you could see.I started writing and didn't stop until i had written 5 two sided pages.This is not the first and only time i've had contact!!I was never afraid,they were friendly!!!!!!!!!!!
content.summary: Woke up at aprox 4am.It was brighter than day i was standing at window saying noi over&over

content.detailedDescription: When i was four years old my family went on a horseback riding trip after lunch at fall creek falls tennessee.  on this trip with me was my mother, father and six year older brother.  i rode in the saddle with my mother while everyone else had their own horse.  at the very start of the horseback riding trip my older brother's horse got spooked and took off down the trail at a fast pace.  my mother who many years of experience riding on horses managed to pull my brother off his horse.  my dad i recall on this trip was yelling at his horse all the time to get back on the trail. after this scare with my brother's horse we asked if we could run on ahead.  we had no interest on getting back on any horses.  after a few minutes my brother and i were alone in the woods.  then everything around us got very quiet and there was an odd feeling of stillness in the air.  my brother got scared and ran back down the trail leaving me all alone.   i then have a memory of a few humanoid looking greyish beings come up to me.  my next memory was being on the edge of the woods with the creatures looking out into a parking lot next to the horse barn.  they were saying i had to return to my family but i recall not wanting to go but wanting to stay with them.   hesitantly i walked out of the woods towards the car.  i looked over my shoulder one time at them and then walked on up to the car.  i was not noticed till i got very close to the car.  my mother years later told me that i was gone for about 45 minutes to an hour and that they were discussing contacting the park ranger to begin to search for me. this was my first experience with the greys that occurred during the "great ufo wave" of october 1973.
content.summary: Abduction at fall creek falls tn

content.detailedDescription:
I was camping at owl canyon about 10 miles north of barstow, ca. i was in my rv sitting in the cockpit watching the stars. no one else was in the campground that i am aware of. the distance between the western and eastern ridges of the canyon is about a quarter of a mile. i was facing toward the south at the open end of the canyon. i observed the first light come over the western ridge. it was followed by 6 more lights. as  the first light got to about half way across the canyon i began to hear a very soft whirring or humming sound. as the first light got over the eastern ridge the last light came over the western ridge. at first, because of the sound and stiffness of the object i thought it might be a blimp. the lights were not that high or that far from me and i am certain it was not a blimp. there was no structure i could see, only lights. i then thought it might be balloons or the lights sometimes released as a celebration. however the lights never wavered and the distance between them was constant. the lights were a bright red and square. they were all equal distance from each other.

                      . 

         .   .   .      .   .

                    .

the dots above show the placement of the lights. i was too awed at the time to think about taking a picture with my phone. the lights were moving right to left in the diagram. the last light farther to the right was blinking. as the lights were over the ridge in the eastern sky they suddenly turned white except for the last one which remained red. then they all suddenly disappeared. i want to emphasize that they stayed rigid and the distance between them was constant but i could determine no structure, just lights. also the movement was very slow, maybe 5 mph or so.
content.summary: Observed lights

content.detailedDescription:
Two of my friends and i were out late in the evening watching the perseid meteor shower, looking towards the northwest. the meteors were pretty scarce but suddenly a bright light appeared that was so unusually bright that it caught our attention. the light appeared and grew in intensity until it was 2-3 times brighter than any star in the sky. it held that intensity for a few seconds and then slowly decreased from intensity until it disappeared. this pulsing repeated three more times and then there was a period of perhaps 8 seconds of darkness and then the pulsing repeated low to high intensity again but the shocking my thing to us to as that instead of moving along a track in the sky (as you would expect a plane or satellite to move) these pulses appeared in exactly the same position. there were in total,  three sets of four pulses which were seperated by the approximately 8 second intervals. 

the intensity of the light, the metronomic pulsing and the fact that it remained stationary was so unusual that none of us could come up with any possible explanation. it was a mind boggling combination. we still talk about it and i decided to file a report in hopes of ci find an explanation or someone else who has seen this phenomenon.
content.summary: Very bright pulsating light  2-3 times brighter than any star in the sky. the light remained perfectly stationary in the same nw location. the pulses  grew in intensity from beginning to end of each set.
